metadata.title: Multichannel Common Depth Point (CDP) Seismic Reflection Data Announcement 1977 (W)  Seismic Data for the Gulf of Alaska

creators.name: Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), National Environmental Satellite, Data
Information Service (NESDIS), National Geophysical Data Center (NGDC)

metadata.description:
As part of a program by the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS), a
number of multichannel common depth point (CDP) seismic
reflection lines were collected from the Alaskan coastal areas.
The National Geophysical and Solar-Terrestrial Data Center of
NOAA is making these data available for general use as they are
released by USGS.  This is to announce the availability of
seismic sections for a number of survey lines in the Gulf of
Alaska.
